Class PhoneNumber

A PhoneNumber stores a formatted phone number in a way that is able to keep all numbers uniform.

Constructors

constructor

  • new PhoneNumber(phoneNumber: string | number): PhoneNumber
    • Defined in contact/PhoneNumber.ts:28

    Creates a PhoneNumber.

    Parameters

    • phoneNumber: string | number

      Either a string or a number. They will be formatted such that they have at least 10 digits, with zeros filling from the left until there are 10 digits as long as the string isn't empty at initalization.

    Returns PhoneNumber

Methods

getFormattedNumber

  • getFormattedNumber(intl?: boolean): string
    • Defined in contact/PhoneNumber.ts:63

    Returns the phone number as a formatted string.

    Parameters

    • Default value intl: boolean = false

      Whether to include the country code when the country code is +1 (USA). Area codes are always returned for non-us numbers.

    Returns string

toString

  • toString(format?: boolean, intl?: boolean): string
    • Defined in contact/PhoneNumber.ts:73

    Returns the full phone number as a string.

    Parameters

    • Default value format: boolean = true

      Whether to format the phone number.

    • Default value intl: boolean = false

      Whether to force a country code. If true, the returned phone number will always have the country code. If false, the returned phone number will only have the code for non-us numbers.

    Returns string
